  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Potential felony prosecution\n- Significant prison time\n- Large monetary fines\n\n2. Federal prosecution\n- Charges under federal money laundering statutes\n- Investigation by agencies like FBI and IRS\n\n3. Potential penalties\n- Prison sentences ranging from 5-20 years\n- Fines up to $500,000 or more\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n\n4. Additional consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n\n5. International implications\n- Potential extradition\n- Global financial sanctions\n- Restrictions on international banking\n\nThe specific outcome depends on the amount of money involved, the method used, and prior criminal history.",
